Program: Great Lives
Title: Millicent Garrett Fawcett
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00771zc
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 27 May 2016
For 50 years, Millicent Garrett Fawcett struggled to win the right to vote for women in Britain, yet today she is little-known compared to the suffragette leaders who took a more militant course. Feminist campaigner Lesley Abdela discusses the extraordinary 'MGF', with Matthew Parris and historian Elizabeth Crawford. Show less